name: Rock Health
tag_list: mobile, accelerator, incubator, healthcare, apps, startups, mentor, mentors
overview:
Rock Health supports innovators working at the intersection of healthcare and technology. Founded in 2010, Rock Health supports health entrepreneurs through a startup accelerator, open-source research and public events.

Rock Health’s accelerator program provides strategic and operational support, mentorship, office space, an elective $100,000 convertible note from the Rock Health Fund, and access to a top-tier network of partners, academic medical centers, and clinicians.

Rock Health partners include Aberdare Ventures, Accel Partners, Fenwick & West, GE, Genentech, Harvard Medical School, Kaiser Permanente, Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers, Mayo Clinic, Mohr Davidow Ventures, Montreux Equity Partners, NEA, Qualcomm, Quest Diagnostics, Silicon Valley Bank, UnitedHealth Group, and UCSF. For more information, visit www.rockhealth.com.
